 These results are important in a few respects. First, the coefficient on the time (popular thing/general way things are going) (T) 
 is negative and highly significant, pointing to/showing that 
 over the past 15 years, yields of RR21 (lowered in number/got worse/gotten worse) at 
 an average once-a-year rate of 6.8% (Fig. 1). This 
 striking rate of decline appears to be due to 
 increasing leaf rust and Helminthosporium leaf 
 disease (chance of being harmed), as well as crop and useful thing/valuable supply 
 management problems on the research farms 
 where the trials were managed and did/done. 9 Second, the 
