 The idea that MVs offer increased protection against sicknesses runs opposite to what people believe now, which hints that traditional wheat varieties gave/given superior resistance (for example, see Shiva, 1991; Conway and Barbier, 
 1990; Berg et aI., 1991; Hobbelink, 1991). In fact, before the 
 Green Revolution losses to sicknesses were often big in 
 many major wheat-growing areas of South Asia (Byerlee, 
 1994). The MVs connected with Nepal's Green Revolution in 
 wheat greatly reduced the risk of disease losses by incorporating resistance (tiny chemical assembly instructions inside of living things)  identified over the course of more than 
 20 years of research in Mexico and in other places. 
